; parchment_theme.tres — canonical UI theme.
;
; Authored: Sprint 10 S10-M1 (2026-05-05).
; Source of truth: design/art/art-bible.md §4 (palette) + §7 (typography / preserving warm miniature).
; Architecture contract: docs/architecture/ADR-0008-ui-framework-dual-focus-parity-and-theme.md.
;
; Loaded once at boot via src/core/scene_manager/main_root.gd:
;   theme = preload("res://assets/ui/parchment_theme.tres")
; Cascades to every Control descendant of MainRoot.
;
; PALETTE (Art Bible §4 — hex → linear-srgb floats below):
;   Guild Amber     #C8872A  Color(0.7843, 0.5294, 0.1647, 1)  player territory / pressed buttons
;   Lantern Gold    #F2B83B  Color(0.9490, 0.7216, 0.2314, 1)  reward / hover accent / identity headers
;   Parchment Cream #EDE0C4  Color(0.9294, 0.8784, 0.7686, 1)  panel ground
;   Dusk Purple     #5B4A72  Color(0.3569, 0.2902, 0.4471, 1)  dungeon / disadvantage
;   Moss Sage       #7A8C5E  Color(0.4784, 0.5490, 0.3686, 1)  forest / nature
;   Ember Rust      #A84C2F  Color(0.6588, 0.2980, 0.1843, 1)  danger
;   Slate Ink       #2C2838  Color(0.1725, 0.1569, 0.2196, 1)  typography / shadow / outline
;
; FONT STRATEGY (reverted 2026-06-03 — playtest legibility fix):
;   No custom font face. The theme specifies font SIZES only; every Control
;   falls back to Godot's built-in default font. The Sprint 20 Lora + IM Fell
;   English wiring was removed because the display face read as "not clear" in
;   playtest. Per DESIGN.md §Typography. (ADR-0008 two-font-max still holds —
;   zero custom fonts ≤ two.)
;
; THEME VARIATIONS:
;   ParchmentPanel    (PanelContainer)  warmer document panel with thicker border
;   IdentityHeader    (Label)           illuminated-manuscript display tier (≥24px floor)
;   SelectedSlotButton (Label)          formation_assignment "Selected" badge — Lantern Gold
;                                       on Parchment Cream with Slate Ink outline.
;                                       Referenced by formation_assignment.gd:245.

[gd_resource type="Theme" load_steps=12 format=3]

; Parchment panel surface — Gemini-generated painterly grain (the FILL) composed
; with a deterministic crisp Slate Ink frame + rounded transparent corners (the
; GEOMETRY) via tools/asset-pipeline/compose_ui_panel.py. Used as a 9-patch
; StyleBoxTexture below (texture_margin = 14 px to match the composed corner zone).
; Resolves OQ-DS-02 → "static PNG texture". See ADR-0023.
[ext_resource type="Texture2D" uid="uid://dxbbhee8ph068" path="res://assets/art/ui/ui_panel_parchment.png" id="1_parchment_tex"]

; --------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Fonts — reverted to Godot's built-in default font (2026-06-03).
; --------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Playtest finding: the IM Fell English display face (and the Lora serif body)
; read as "not clear." Per user decision, the game now uses Godot's built-in
; default font everywhere — the theme specifies NO font face, so every Control
; falls back to the engine default sans-serif. Font SIZES and colors are
; unchanged; only the typeface reverts.
;
; The Lora + IM Fell English TTFs remain on disk at res://assets/fonts/
; (now unreferenced) in case a future polish pass wants a custom face — re-wire
; via FontFile ext_resources + FontVariation sub_resources + a default_font line.
; Supersedes the Sprint 20 S20-M2 Lora/IM-Fell wiring. See DESIGN.md §Typography.

; --------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Panel styleboxes
; --------------------------------------------------------------------------

; Default panel — neutral parchment ground with thin Slate Ink border.
; Used by Panel + PanelContainer (default Control class).
; NOTE: StyleBoxTexture (parchment 9-patch) — was StyleBoxFlat (flat cream) until
; OQ-DS-02 resolved to a static PNG. Texture carries the baked 2px Slate Ink border
; + 6px rounded transparent corners; content_margins preserve the prior padding.
; StyleBoxTexture has no drop shadow — the ink border + grain define the panel edge.
[sub_resource type="StyleBoxTexture" id="panel_default"]
content_margin_left = 12.0
content_margin_top = 10.0
content_margin_right = 12.0
content_margin_bottom = 10.0
texture = ExtResource("1_parchment_tex")
texture_margin_left = 14.0
texture_margin_top = 14.0
texture_margin_right = 14.0
texture_margin_bottom = 14.0

; ParchmentPanel theme variation — warmer document panel.
; Thicker Slate Ink border + extra padding + soft warm vignette via shadow.
; Use via panel.theme_type_variation = &"ParchmentPanel" or
; UIFramework.apply_parchment_panel(panel) once that helper lands (S10-M2).
; StyleBoxTexture (parchment 9-patch) — same texture as panel_default; the warmer
; ParchmentPanel register now comes from extra content padding (18/14 vs 12/10)
; rather than a thicker drawn border. Was StyleBoxFlat (2px border + amber shadow).
[sub_resource type="StyleBoxTexture" id="panel_parchment"]
content_margin_left = 18.0
content_margin_top = 14.0
content_margin_right = 18.0
content_margin_bottom = 14.0
texture = ExtResource("1_parchment_tex")
texture_margin_left = 14.0
texture_margin_top = 14.0
texture_margin_right = 14.0
texture_margin_bottom = 14.0

